          "text": [
            "> Input: 1/4 c. water, 2 c. sugar, 1 green bell pepper, chopped, 1 c. celery, chopped, 3/4 c. vinegar, 1 can sauerkraut, thoroughly drained, 1 large onion, chopped, 1 jar pimento (middle size)\n",
            "= Target: Boil water, vinegar and sugar and let cool. Place chopped ingredients and pimento in mixing bowl with lid. Mix with sauerkraut. Pour liquid over all and marinate 24 hours. Will keep in refrigerator for 2 weeks.\n",
            "< Output: combine water , sugar , vinegar and celery seed . bring to a boil over medium heat , stirring constantly , until mixture boils . add celery , onion and bell pepper and mix . pour into a serving bowl and refrigerate overnight . <EOS>\n",
            "----------------------------------------\n",
            "> Input: 3 c. sugar, 6 c. water, 1 (46 oz.) can pineapple juice, unsweetened, 5 ripe bananas, 5 oranges or 2 c. orange juice concentrate, juice of 2 lemons\n",
            "= Target: Boil 3 minutes the sugar and water. Let cool. Add pineapple juice. Mix in blender the bananas, oranges and orange juice, lemon juice and red food coloring. After blending, add this to first mixture. Mix thoroughly and freeze in milk cartons (plastic jugs). When ready to serve, take out of freezer and partly thaw. Before serving, add 3 quarts Slice or ginger ale. This makes 1 gallon plus 1 quart. Serves 50.\n",
            "< Output: combine sugar and water . bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute . remove from heat . add orange juice , orange juice and orange juice . mix well and pour over ice cream . freeze until ready to serve . <EOS>\n",
            "----------------------------------------\n",
            "> Input: 3 c. torn lettuce, 1 (5 oz.) can white chicken, drained, 1 medium apple, sliced, coarsely chopped or half walnuts, 1/2 c. seedless red grapes, cut in half, 1/4 c. Ranch or Blue cheese dressing\n",
            "= Target: Mix together and serve.\n",
            "< Output: combine all ingredients in a large salad bowl . mix well and chill . serve with crackers . <EOS>\n",
            "----------------------------------------\n",
            "> Input: 2 c. lime, 1 gal. sliced cucumbers, 9 c. sugar (5 lb.), 3 pt. apple cider vinegar, 2 tsp. celery seed, 2 tsp. pickling spice, whole cloves, 3 cinnamon sticks, salt\n",
            "= Target: Mix lime and 2 gallons of water; soak cucumbers in solution for 24 hours. Drain and rinse well. Soak 2 to 3 hours more in plain water; drain. Make a syrup of sugar, apple cider vinegar, and celery seed; bring to a boil and pour over cucumbers. Let stand 12 hours. Add pickling spice, a few cloves, cinnamon sticks and salt. Boil 20 minutes. Pack in jars and seal. Wonderful!\n",
            "< Output: combine all ingredients in a large bowl . bring to a boil . reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour . <EOS>\n",
            "----------------------------------------\n",
            "> Input: 1 c. bourbon (any inexpensive kind), 1 c. soy sauce, 1/2 lb. brown sugar, 1/2 c. lemon juice (fresh), 1 Tbsp. minced garlic, 1 small yellow onion, diced\n",
            "= Target: Mix all ingredients; add steaks and marinate for minimum of 4 hours, overnight is great, turning once. Grill.\n",
            "< Output: combine all ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes . serve over ice . makes 2 cups . <EOS>\n",
            "----------------------------------------\n",
            "> Input: 1/2 c. diced ham, 1/2 c. green onion (green only), 1/2 block grated Cheddar cheese, 1/2 c. chopped olives, 1/2 tsp. curry powder\n",
            "= Target: Mix together with enough mayonnaise to make a spread. Spread on rye bread or sourdough bread and broil until bubbly. You can adjust the curry to your taste.\n",
            "< Output: combine all ingredients and chill . serve with crackers or chips . <EOS>\n",
            "----------------------------------------\n",
            "> Input: 6 large cooking apples, 1/4 lb. castor sugar, 1 Tbsp. sugar, 1 egg, 1 Tbsp. rum, crushed vanilla stick, bread crumbs, 1/2 pt. whipped cream\n",
            "= Target: Bake apples and put through a sieve. Mix the crushed pineapple with sugar and stir into apple puree. Add rum and egg white. Stir until smooth.\n",
            "< Output: cut apples into small pieces . combine sugar , egg and egg . beat egg whites until stiff . fold in whipped cream . pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish . <EOS>\n",
            "----------------------------------------\n",
            "> Input: 1 lb. ground beef, 1/4 c. chopped onions, 1 (8 oz.) can tomatoes, 1 (6 oz.) can tomato paste, 1 tsp. salt, 1/2 tsp. chili powder, 1/4 lb. pasteurized processed cheese, sliced\n",
            "= Target: Brown ground beef in skillet. Drain off excess fat. Add onion and cook until tender. Blend in tomatoes, tomato paste, salt and chili powder. Spread half of meat mixture in 1-quart casserole dish. Arrange half of cheese slices over meat mixture. Top with remaining meat mixture.\n",
            "< Output: brown ground beef and onions . drain off fat and add tomatoes , tomato paste , chili powder , salt and chili powder . simmer for 20 minutes , stirring occasionally . serve with chips . <EOS>\n",
            "----------------------------------------\n",
            "> Input: 2 c. white sugar, 4 tsp. cocoa, 1 stick margarine, 1/2 c. milk, 3 c. quick oatmeal, 1/3 c. peanut butter\n",
            "= Target: Bring to boil and boil 2 minutes. Take from heat and add 3 cups quick oatmeal and 1/3 cup peanut butter. Drop on wax paper by spoonful.\n",
            "< Output: mix sugar , cocoa , margarine and milk . bring to a boil and boil for 2 minutes , then add oatmeal and oatmeal . mix well . drop by spoonfuls on wax paper . <EOS>\n",
            "----------------------------------------\n",
